{%- comment -%}
  Renders a star rating + review count for the current product.

  Reads from Shopify's review metafields, which is the standard
  contract used by Judge.me, Loox, Shopify Product Reviews, and
  most other rating apps:
    product.metafields.reviews.rating.value      → Object{rating, scale_max}
    product.metafields.reviews.rating_count      → Number (or Metafield)

  If the rating metafield is missing or empty, the block silently
  renders nothing — important for new stores that haven't set up
  reviews yet, since we never want to show a fake "0 stars (0)"
  widget.

  Defensive read for rating_count:
    Different review apps store this metafield slightly differently —
    some return a plain Number, others return a Metafield wrapper
    where the integer is at .value. We check both, falling back to
    0 if neither produces a value.

  Visuals: two layers of identical star rows. The bottom layer is
  the empty (outlined) stars in muted colour; the top layer is the
  filled stars in foreground colour, clipped to a width corresponding
  to the rating percentage. This gives clean half-star and decimal
  precision (e.g. 4.3 → 86% wide) without rendering different SVGs
  per fractional value.

  Accepts:
    product  {Product}  required — for the metafields
    block    {Block}    required — for shopify_attributes
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign rating_obj = product.metafields.reviews.rating.value

  # Defensive read: rating_count may be a plain integer OR a Metafield
  # object whose value is at .value, depending on the review app.
  assign rating_count_meta = product.metafields.reviews.rating_count
  assign rating_count = 0
  if rating_count_meta.value
    assign rating_count = rating_count_meta.value
  elsif rating_count_meta != blank
    assign rating_count = rating_count_meta
  endif
-%}

{%- if rating_obj != blank and rating_obj.rating != blank -%}
  {%- liquid
    assign rating_value = rating_obj.rating | times: 1.0
    assign scale_max = rating_obj.scale_max | default: 5
    if scale_max == 0
      assign scale_max = 5
    endif
    assign percent = rating_value | times: 100 | divided_by: scale_max
  -%}
  <div
    class="valor-mp__rating"
    {{ block.shopify_attributes }}
  >
    <div
      class="valor-mp__rating-stars"
      role="img"
      aria-label="{{ 'product.rating' | t: rating: rating_value, scale: scale_max }}"
      style="--valor-rating-percent: {{ percent }}%;"
    >
      <div class="valor-mp__rating-stars-empty" aria-hidden="true">★★★★★</div>
      <div class="valor-mp__rating-stars-filled" aria-hidden="true">★★★★★</div>
    </div>
    {%- if rating_count > 0 -%}
      <span class="valor-mp__rating-text">
        {{- rating_value }} ({{ rating_count -}})
      </span>
    {%- else -%}
      <span class="valor-mp__rating-text">
        {{- rating_value -}}
      </span>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
{%- endif -%}
